    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But isn't \"professionalism\" just a social construct? If they both solve the customer's problem effectively, does the dialect really matter? It feels like you're saying someone who speaks differently is inherently a worse worker even if their logic and problem-solving skills are identical to someone using Standard English.",
